<!-- Write your raw requirements below this line. -->

- Build a local meal planner desktop app (web-based, runs locally) served on port 8010 using a simple Node.js + Express server started with `npm start` or `node server.js`.

- Create a single-page frontend (plain HTML/CSS/JS, no framework) with a tab or section navigation between: Profile, Meal Log, and Add Meal.

- Add a Profile form where the user can input: weight (kg), height (cm), age, sex, primary goal (lose weight / maintain / gain muscle / eat healthier), preferred diet (balanced / mediterranean / low carb / vegetarian / vegan / etc.), activity level, food allergies or restrictions, and optional notes.

- All user data (profile + meal log) must be persisted locally in a `data.json` file in the project root — no database, no cloud storage.

- Expose a REST API with these endpoints: `GET /api/profile`, `POST /api/profile`, `GET /api/meals`, `POST /api/meals`, `DELETE /api/meals/:id` — all reading/writing to `data.json`.

- Create an Add Meal form with fields: meal name, meal type (breakfast / lunch / dinner / snack), date (defaults to today), calories (kcal, optional), protein in grams (optional), description or ingredients (optional), and a "how did it feel?" mood selector.

- Display the Meal Log as a list of logged meals showing name, type tag, date, calories, protein, and mood — with a remove button per entry.

- On the Profile tab, if weight + height + age + sex + activity level are all provided, compute and display the estimated daily calorie target using the Mifflin-St Jeor formula adjusted for goal (−300 kcal for weight loss, +250 kcal for muscle gain).

- The app must start cleanly with `node server.js` and serve the frontend as a static file from a `/public` folder — no build step required.

- NFR: The app must load and be interactive in under 1 second on localhost. No external runtime dependencies beyond `express`.
